      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOD'S RAPTURE (6) drops back to a much easier race today after tackling Open 3YO company through the beginning of this preparation. Back to 1200m today and gets Pike on board as well, who was on board for her only victory. Just needs to hold her form back in grade to be winning. DELTASON (1) is a handy type, winning over this track and trip last campaign, though he resumes here without a trial and is 0/2 fresh. That being said, he did jump a $7.50 chance in the Fairetha when not disgraced at Listed level. Drawn well and can make an impression. MY DANNY BOY (7) has been impressive this campaign, winning two back before being caught very late last time out. He draws well again to find the front with the claim of Nottle being very important with his racing pattern. Can return to winning ways. VANDOULA JET (8) gets the Blinkers on for the first time today and can put her best foot forward. HURRICANE HARLEY (2) can improve back in grade.",
